Since $L$ is divisible by $3$, we can rewrite the equations as:
\begin{align*} 1 &\equiv 1 \pmod h \\ 2 &\equiv 1 \pmod h \\ 3 &\equiv 1 \pmod h \\ &\ \ \vdots \\ L &\equiv 1 \pmod h \end{align*}
